OL,3,CPupil told self, 'What am I doing,
OL,4,Cstop' during school stabbing
OL,6,FEarlier, the court heard how the
OL,7,Fdefendant had been carrying knives
OL,8,Fsince being in primary school.
OL,10,FAsked by the defence barrister how
OL,11,Foften she took a knife to school the
OL,12,Fgirl replied every day since she was
OL,13,Fin "Year three or four", saying she
OL,14,Ffelt "scared and worried" and used
OL,15,Fknives to self-harm.
OL,17,FEarlier in the trial the court heard
OL,18,Fthe defendant had been found with a
OL,19,Fkitchen knife in her bag at the start
OL,20,Fof the school year in September 2023
OL,21,Fby Ms Elias.
