OL,3,CPupil told self, 'What am I doing,
OL,4,Cstop' during school stabbing
OL,6,FExplaining the incident, she said she
OL,7,Fhad forgotten she had it in her
OL,8,Fpossession, having used it to carve
OL,9,Fher name into a tree.
OL,11,FShe was suspended from Ysgol Dyffryn
OL,12,FAman for a week but was allowed to
OL,13,Freturn on the condition her father
OL,14,Fchecked her school belongings each
OL,15,Fmorning and removed dangerous knives
OL,16,Ffrom the family home.
OL,18,FThe pupil's father failed to carry out
OL,19,Fthe check on the morning of April
OL,20,F24th, with his daughter taking his
OL,21,Fmulti-tool knife he used for fishing.
