OL,3,CPupil told self, 'What am I doing,
OL,4,Cstop' during school stabbing
OL,6,FFollowing a dispute with Ms Elias,
OL,7,Fwhich centred around her not being
OL,8,Fallowed in a school hall during break
OL,9,Ftime, the defendant launched an attack
OL,10,Fwhich left Ms Elias with stab wounds
OL,11,Fto her arms and hand.
OL,13,FMs Hopkin intervened to try and
OL,14,Fretrieve the knife but was stabbed in
OL,15,Fthe neck, the defendant then ran and
OL,16,Fstabbed a fellow pupil in the
OL,17,Fshoulder, the jury heard, while
OL,18,Fscreaming "you're next".
